            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-69" n="69"><lb/>I ne'er could endure my Talent to smother;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-70" n="70">I told you one Tale; I'll tell you another:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-71" n="71">A <hi rend="italics">Joyner</hi>, to fasten a <hi rend="italics">Saint</hi> in a <hi rend="italics">Nitch</hi>,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-72" n="72">Bor'd a large <hi rend="italics">Auger-Hole</hi> in the Image's Breech:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-73" n="73">But finding the <hi rend="italics">Statue</hi> to make no Complaint,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-74" n="74">He would ne'er be convinc'd it was a <hi rend="italics">true Saint</hi>:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-75" n="75">When the <hi rend="italics">true Wood</hi> arrives, as he soon will no doubt</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-76" n="76">(For that's but a Sham <note place="foot">·<hi rend="italics">The Effigies of Mr. </hi>Wood<hi rend="italics"> has been frequently carried about in Procession, and burnt</hi>.</note> Wood they carry about)</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-77" n="77">What <hi rend="italics">Stuff</hi> he is made on, you quickly may find,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-78" n="78">If you make the same Trial, and <hi rend="italics">bore</hi> him <hi rend="italics">behind</hi>:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-79" n="79">I'll hold you a Groat, when you <hi rend="italics">wimble</hi> his <hi rend="italics">Bum</hi>,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-80" n="80">He'll bellow as loud as the <hi rend="italics">De'il</hi> in a <hi rend="italics">Drum</hi>.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-81" n="81">From me, I declare, you shall have no Denial,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-82" n="82">And there can be no harm in making a Trial:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-83" n="83">And, when to the Joy of your Hearts, he has roar'd,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-334-24XA-line-84" n="84">You may shew him about for a new <hi rend="italics">Groaning Board</hi>.</l>
